                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, strong red.</seg>
                        Scribe: Baḥrǝyä Śǝllāse. Baḥrǝyä
                        Śǝllāse is mentioned as the scribe in Additio 3.<date>Second half of 20th
                           century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the King, Patriarch and
                           Bishop; incipit of Texts I-II; titles of books to be read; initial word
                           or line of the passages to be read; directives to the ministers; some
                           letters of the Trinitarian formula (alternating with black letters) (in
                           fols. 23r, 42r); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 On the incipit pages of Texts I-II (fols. 3r, 45r) a few
                           lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from an unidentified text.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: ዊኀዊሃ፡ ወታበልዖ፡ ፍኅርቱ፡ ለመርዓዊሃ፡ ወነኪርሰ፡
                              ኢይጥሰም፡ እምነሁ፡ እስመ፡ ኢተውህበ፡ ሎቱ፡ ለመርዓዊ፡ መኑ፡ ዘርእየ፡ መርዓዊ፡ ዘይጠባሕ፡ ሥጋሁ፡ በጊዜ፡
                              ከብካቡ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a secondary hand (?). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus from="42rb15" to="42va14">f. 42rb, l.15-42va, l.14</locus>
                           <desc>: Supplication.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the same hand as that of the main text. Supplication
                              for several individuals whose the donor, Walatta Śǝllāse (s. Additio
                              3). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus from="42vb6" to="43ra4">f. 42vb, l.6-43ra, l.4</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#42vb">42vb</locus>, l.6: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘወይዘሮ፡ ወለተ፡ መስቀል፡
                              ኃይሉ፡ ዘአጥ{ረ}የታ፡ በንዋያ፡ ወወሀበቶ፡ ለአብነ፡ ገብረ፡ ገብረ[sic.]፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱ{ስ}፡ ዘአናማዕፃ፡
                              ከመ፡ ይኩና፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ዘሠረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ በሰልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዞ፡
                                 [<locus target="#43ra">43ra</locus>] ይኩን፡ አሜን። ጸሐፊሃ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወዝልጉስ፡
                              አባ፡ ባሕርየ፡ ሥላሴ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the same hand as that of the main text. The name of the
                              donor, Walatta Masqal, is mentioned like the name of the church to
                              which the Ms. was originally donated (?),ʾOna Maʿṣo Gabra Manfas
                              Qǝddus, and the name of the scribe, Baḥrǝyä Śǝllāse. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#45ra">ff. 45ra-45</locus>
                           <desc>vb: Excerpt from the Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass”.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                     </list>
